      section
        h2 Windows XP boot process
          h3 
            ul
              li System power up, inisialisasi video (tampilan) dan test hardware (termasuk memori). Proses ini disebut dengan POST (Power On Self Test)
              li Selesai POST, system membaca setiap adapter dan biasanya dilakukan oleh BIOS.
              li System boot loader membaca boot sector atau MBR (Master Boot Record)
              li MBR membaca file NTLDR dan mempass nya ke NTLDR
              li NTLDR berubah ke mode 32  bit(intel x86 selalu memboot di dalam mode 16 bit). Kemudian membaca boot.ini
              li Di dalam boot ini terkandung informasi tentang operating system yang bisa diload (dijalankan)
      section      
              li Kemudian NTLDR akan menjalankan ntdetect.com Tugas ntdetect adalah membaca informasi hardware dan menyimpan ke HKLM/Hardware. Kemudian process dipass kembali ke NTLDR.
              li NTLDR kemudian menjalankan  Windows NT Kernel, menjalankan services dan start Windows.
              li Pada waktu kernel dijalankan, maka ada menjalankan juga HAL (Hardware Abstraction Layer) yg digunakan untuk menjalankan service/konfigurasi perangkat keras.
              li Registry HKLM\_System dibaca ke memory. Semua driver kemudian dibaca.
              li Sesudah itu maka kemudian Windows XP dimulai tergantung dari setting startup yg dijalankan dan masuk ke WinLogon.
      section
        h2 Lokasi dari File Registry
        h3 %systemroot%\System32\Config
        table(width="600" style="text-align:left")
          tr
            td
              p - autoexec.nt The file that initializes the MS-DOS environment unless a different startup file is specified in an application's PIF.
              p - config.nt The file that initializes the MS-DOS environment unless a different startup file is
              specified in an application's PIF.
              p - Default The default registry file.
              p - SAM The SAM (Security Accounts Manager) registry file.
              p - Security The security registry file.
              p - Software The application software registry file.
              p - System The system registry file.
      section
        h3 In a typical Windows XP installation, the %SystemRoot%\System32\Config directory contains these files:
        table(width="600" style="text-align:left")
          tr
            td
              p AppEvent.evt The application(s) event log file.
              p DEF$$$$$.del The default registry recovery file.
              p Default The default registry file.
              p Default.sav A backup copy of the information contained in the default registry file.
              p DnsEvent.evt The DNS server event log.
              p File Rep.evt One of two File Replication Service event log files.
              p Netlogon.dnb A NetLogon support file.
              p Netlogon.dns A NetLogon support file.
              p NTDS.evt The Windows XP directory service event log.
              p NtFrs.evt The second of two File Replication Service event log files.
      section
          h3
            table(width="600" style="text-align:left")
              tr
                td
                  p - SAM The Security Accounts Manager registry file.
                  p - SecEvent.evt The security event log.
                  p - Security The security registry file.
                  p - SOF$$$$$.del The software registry recovery file.
                  p - Software The application software registry file.
                  p - Software.sav A backup copy of the information contained in the software registry file.
                  p - SYS$$$$$.del The system registry recovery file.
                  p - SysEvent.evt The system events log.
                  p - System The system registry file.
                  p - System.alt A copy of the information contained in the system registry file.
                  p - System.sav A backup copy of the information contained in the system registry file.
                  p - Userdiff The file that migrates preexisting user profiles from previous versions of Windows
                  NT to Windows XP.
